<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<tt xml:lang="en-US"
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/ns/ttml"
  xmlns:ttm="http://www.w3.org/ns/ttml#metadata"
  xmlns:tts="http://www.w3.org/ns/ttml#styling">
  <head>
    <metadata xmlns:ttm="http://www.w3.org/ns/ttml#metadata">
      <ttm:title>445101852 - 1_el2vr4da - PID 1530551</ttm:title>
    </metadata>
    <styling>
      <style xml:id="basic" tts:textAlign="center" />
    </styling>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.000" end="00:00:03.880" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visors. You've arrived at the
<br />second base camp,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:03.880" end="00:00:07.760" tts:direction="ltr">where you're going to focus on the various
<br />chart kinds that you can make</p>
        <p begin="00:00:07.760" end="00:00:12.170" tts:direction="ltr">within tableau and also use in any kind of
<br />visualization.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:12.170" end="00:00:14.580" tts:direction="ltr">So here is our journey,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:14.580" end="00:00:19.320" tts:direction="ltr">and you've been well on your way to
<br />learning all about PAC,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:19.320" end="00:00:23.660" tts:direction="ltr">and now you're adding in that K with that
<br />second base camp.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:23.660" end="00:00:26.040" tts:direction="ltr">Here's what you'll do in this base camp.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:26.040" end="00:00:29.960" tts:direction="ltr">You'll continue your learning by
<br />understanding the chart kinds.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:29.960" end="00:00:33.880" tts:direction="ltr">You'll also have a chart kind knowledge
<br />check so that</p>
        <p begin="00:00:33.880" end="00:00:37.940" tts:direction="ltr">we know that it's moved from short term
<br />memory to long term memory.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:37.940" end="00:00:41.200" tts:direction="ltr">You'll have a chance to do another data
<br />talk, and of course,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:41.200" end="00:00:45.580" tts:direction="ltr">you'll have a chance to apply your
<br />knowledge through the second challenge.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:45.580" end="00:00:50.120" tts:direction="ltr">This base camp, you'll accomplish these
<br />three objectives.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:50.120" end="00:00:52.580" tts:direction="ltr">You'll be able to classify and understand</p>
        <p begin="00:00:52.580" end="00:00:56.120" tts:direction="ltr">the different chart types based on their
<br />appropriate use cases.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:56.120" end="00:00:58.760" tts:direction="ltr">You're going to be able to compare and
<br />contrast</p>
        <p begin="00:00:58.760" end="00:01:02.900" tts:direction="ltr">those strengths and those limitations of
<br />those chart kinds.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:02.900" end="00:01:08.260" tts:direction="ltr">Then you'll be able to justify why you've
<br />selected one chart over another.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:08.260" end="00:01:10.100" tts:direction="ltr">It's important to be able to have this in</p>
        <p begin="00:01:10.100" end="00:01:13.200" tts:direction="ltr">your toolbox so that you can use that in</p>
        <p begin="00:01:13.200" end="00:01:15.440" tts:direction="ltr">your presentation and visualization skills
<br />to</p>
        <p begin="00:01:15.440" end="00:01:20.060" tts:direction="ltr">optimize your data visualization. Happy
<br />visit.</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</tt>
